<!-- ===============================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The southern Brisbane suburb that families and investors pursue for its multicultural food precinct, strong rental demand, motorway access, and a community character unlike anywhere else in the city.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Sunnybank sits approximately thirteen kilometres south of the Brisbane CBD, positioned in Brisbane's southern residential corridor with direct Pacific Motorway access and a suburb identity that is genuinely distinct from its neighbours. The suburb has built a national reputation as one of Australia's great multicultural food destinations, with a concentration of Asian restaurants, fresh produce markets, and specialty grocers that draw visitors from across Brisbane and make day-to-day living here a different proposition from the purely residential suburbs that surround it. Buyers in 2026 are making a deliberate choice when they target Sunnybank, and that choice reflects a clear understanding of what this address offers that others in the southern corridor do not.
    </p>
