    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Pacific Motorway interchange provides residents with direct access to the Brisbane CBD and the Gold Coast, and the Garden City shopping centre in neighbouring Upper Mount Gravatt adds major retail and dining amenity that complements the suburb's own commercial precinct. For families, the combination of the food precinct, local parks, and established school catchments makes Sunnybank a genuinely functional place to raise children. For investors, the suburb's consistent tenant demand, its diverse buyer pool at resale, and its position in the southern residential corridor make it a practical long-term holding.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The housing stock in Sunnybank includes a mix of established family homes, units, and townhouses that reflects the suburb's dual appeal to owner-occupiers and investors. Properties that present well, sit on workable land configurations, and are correctly priced against recent comparable sales consistently attract strong buyer competition. Sellers who understand the specific profile of buyers targeting Sunnybank are better positioned to prepare and market their property in a way that resonates with that demand.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
